==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Estovers
<hw>Es*to"vers</hw> <pr>(⟦ecr⟧s*t⟦omac⟧"v⟦etil⟧rz)</pr>, <pos>n.
pl.</pos> <ety>[OF. <ets>estoveir</ets>, <ets>estovoir</ets>, necessary,
necessity, need, prop. an infin. meaning to suit, be fit, be necessary.
See <er>Stover</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Law)</fld> <def>Necessaries or
supplies; an allowance to a person out of an estate or other thing for
support; as of wood to a tenant for life, etc., of sustenance to a man
confined for felony out of his estate, or alimony to a woman divorced
out of her husband's estate.</def> <rj><au>Blackstone.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Common of estovers</b></col>. <cd>See under
<er>Common</er>, <pos>n.</pos></cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Estrade</ent>⟦br⟧
